parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to not operate properly in any mode of 4-wheel drive, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle violently jerks at slow speed while turning
the transfer case fails during hard braking in wet conditions
the vehicle is unable to operate properly in any mode of 4-wheel drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to be unable to stop in an emergency braking situation, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Soft brake pedal pressure
the brakes have to be pumped to get enough braking power to stop the vehicle
the rear brakes wear at a much greater rate than the front brakes
the rear rotors are warped
the rear brakes stick at a stop and release when the throttle is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front differential can cause the vehicle to surge and leak fluid, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle surges
an abnormal sound comes from the vehicle
fluid leaks from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission oil cooler line can cause the vehicle to stop accelerating, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission oil coolant rubs against the engine oil coolant line
causing one or both lines to leak out
the vehicle will just stop accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission shifter can cause the vehicle to not allow the driver to lock the vehicle, and may lead to unexpected shifting or loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Receiving "Shift to Park" messages
inability to lock the vehicle
having to wiggle the shifter to clear the message
unexpected engagement of the electronic parking brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic parking brake can cause the brake to engage unexpectedly, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving at speed.
symptoms: Electronic parking brake engages unexpectedly
vehicle feels and sounds as though the parking brake has been applied
intermittent occurrence of the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intentional Power Reduction by Onboard Computer
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intentional power reduction by the onboard computer can cause a loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when merging onto a busy road or highway.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
inability to accelerate
warning messages or lights indicating a repair is needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tailgate Open Message and Unintended Tailgate Opening
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended opening of the tailgate can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to loss of cargo or trailer detachment, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Receiving tailgate open messages despite the tailgate being closed
tailgate opening unexpectedly while towing a trailer
damage to the tailgate or surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the backup camera guidelines can cause difficulty when reversing, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Backup camera guidelines do not line up center with the vehicle
making it difficult to judge distances and reversing trajectory.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unprotected Framing Piece in Truck Bed
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unprotected framing piece in the truck bed can cause damage to the vehicle, lead to rust, and potentially compromise the security of the vehicle.
symptoms: Small objects
such as keys
can fall into the framing piece and become lodged
potentially causing damage or rust; debris
moisture
or water can enter the framing piece
increasing the likelihood of rust.
